Aedeagus (
Figs. 8–9
) of very characteristic shape, median lobe slender in basal part, weakly dilated in apical third. In lateral view, the endophallus armature is approximately as long as the spoon-like apex. Latter nearly perpendicularly truncate in lateral view while curved to left side and broadly rounded in dorsal view. Ventral flattening of the median lobe rather weak. Parameres thick, arched; with rather broadly rounded apices, each bearing 4-5 apical setae; ventral processus on the left paramere well-developed.
